body.description: Keep players SAFE! This Coach’s and Sports Team First Aid Kit aid designed to treat sports injuries and other recreational activities. It contains first aid essentials for your sports emergencies.Manufactured by the #1 leading Brand in First Aid Kits and Emergency Essentials in the USA. Be Smart Get Prepared 73-piece Coach’s and Team First Aid Kit meets the United States FDA regulatory standards as a medical device and features comprehensive components ideal for cuts, abrasions, sprains, and aches.Custom "roll out" bag can be hung, or rolled out on the ground for easy access to your first aid components. The bag can be rolled up for easy storage (4.5in x 10in x 4.25in), and opened up to 2.75in x10in x16in.This multi-purpose Coach’s and Team Sports First Aid Kit contain the following: CLEAN• 6 Alcohol Wipes• 6 Antiseptic TowelettesTREAT• 2 Antibiotic Ointment Packets • 2 Aspirin Tablets • 2 Ibuprofen Tablets • 2 Instant Cold Compress 5” x 6”PROTECT• 1 Moleskin 2” x 2” • 15 Adhesive Bandages ¾” x 3” • 10 Adhesive Bandages 3/8” x 1 ½” • Cohesive Wrap 2” x 5” yards • 1 Elastic Wrap 2” • 1 Adhesive Tape Roll 5” x 5yards • 4 Sterile Gauze Pads 2” x 2” • 4 Sterile Gauze Pads 4” x 4”• 1 Gauze Roll 2” x 4.1 yardsADDITIONAL SUPPLIES• 10 Cotton Tip Applicators• 2 Nitrile Examination Gloves• 1 Metal Scissor• 1 Plastic Tweezers• First Aid Guide Booklet

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice little kit
reviews.reviewText: My son coaches 5 year olds. I purchased this and some splints to pack in his equipment bag. He liked that it was a roll out and can see everything in each section. All the basics needed (except splints) for sports. I'm going to order one for home and customize it....because I really liked the roll style and easy organization to find what's needed quickly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Brilliant! For coaches, camping, RVs, CERT team, office, at home...
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a first aid kit for my CERT team pack, but I'm also an avid hiker/camper. Most kits are a single pouch and I'm constantly digging through stuff to find what I need. This kit, built like a travel toiletry kit, is BRILLIANT! Hangs up, so it stays out of the dirt. Organized into separate compartments and visible, so I can go immediately to what I'm looking for.There was a handy reference page to help you locate what was there and just enough room to add your specific items and still get it rolled up.I bought multiples. Love these!
